The title of the work "Hitoner" would be equivalent to how "skinnie" is used as a play on "furry".

"Kemono" means "beast". And a "Kemoner" is someone who loves "beast" culture. So a furry.
"Hito" means "human/man". So someone who loves humans would be a "Hitoner".
So a skinnie.

It's not a real word so the tweeter is amused at the concept of using "skinnie" to describe an anthro who loves humans like humans love anthros.
Thar's what I managed to scrap together from a bunch of google searches at least. I think it might be the first time it's been used so I hope due to its popularity the "hitoner" genre picks up over there.
